Key Match Events: Patson Daka scored a header in the 89th minute to secure a 1-1 equalizer for Zambia.
Simon Msuva scored a clinical finish in the 11th minute to give Tanzania the lead.
Post-Match Reflections: Zambia remains third in Group F, while Tanzania's chances of moving to the next round are looking doubtful.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played in the Africa Cup of Nations Group F encounter.
Others: Zambia's Clatous Chama delivered a precision cross from a corner kick that found the head of Patson Daka.
Both teams made substitutions in a strategic bid to secure victory.
